question_content.description:
### Problem10


Let A and B be two decision problems. Suppose we know that A polynomial-time reduces to B. Which of the following can we infer? Mark all that apply.

**Choices:**

A. A and B cannot both be NP-complete

B. If A is in P, then B is in P

C. If A is NP-complete and B is in NP, then B is NP-complete

D. If B is in P, then A is in P 

E. If B is NP-complete then so is A

F. If A is NP-complete then so is B

G. If B is NP-complete and A is in NP then A is NP-complete  

*From Coursera lecture quiz*
choices: A. A and B cannot both be NP-complete
B. If A is in P, then B is in P
C. If A is NP-complete and B is in NP then B is NP-complete
D. If B is in P, then A is in P
E. If B is NP-complete then so is A
F. If A is NP-complete then so is B
G. If B is NP-complete and A is in NP then A is NP-complete
